# Element & geometry conventions

## Mutations

- Update element properties through `mutateElement` in `packages/excalidraw/element/mutateElement.ts` — do not mutate element objects in place elsewhere.

## Geometry

- Use `@excalidraw/math` helpers (`pointFrom`, `pointRotateRads`, `polygon`, etc.) — do not hand-roll rotation math.
- Hit detection shapes come from `getElementShape()` / `getPolygonShape()` in `packages/excalidraw/shapes.tsx` and `packages/utils/geometry/shape.ts`.
- Rotation for hit testing must stay consistent between polygon shapes and collision distance checks (`packages/excalidraw/element/collision.ts`, `distance.ts`).

## Tests (required for element fixes)

Any fix under `packages/excalidraw/element/` or `packages/utils/geometry/` **must** include a Vitest regression test.

```bash
# Targeted suites
yarn test packages/utils/geometry --watch=false
yarn test packages/excalidraw/tests/selection.test.tsx --watch=false
```

Prefer a unit test on the geometry helper when possible; add an integration test if the bug is selection-specific.
